1
00:00:37,100 --> 00:00:41,200
(Touch Your Heart)

2
00:00:41,633 --> 00:00:43,500
(Episode 14)

3
00:00:46,066 --> 00:00:47,200
Um, please wait!

4
00:01:09,766 --> 00:01:11,153
Mr. Kwon Jung-rok?

5
00:01:11,233 --> 00:01:12,866
He's not in the office right now.

6
00:01:13,400 --> 00:01:15,386
No, we have nothing to
say about that.

7
00:01:15,466 --> 00:01:16,566
I'm sorry.

8
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:22,720
Gosh, it's started again
this morning!

9
00:01:22,800 --> 00:01:26,320
I hope today doesn't just end at
just answering complaint calls.

10
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:28,353
Our server is down, too.

11
00:01:28,433 --> 00:01:31,553
What if this ends up on the
National Petition webboard?

12
00:01:31,633 --> 00:01:33,386
Gosh, what do we do?

13
00:01:33,466 --> 00:01:35,586
Our number of clients has
dropped so much as well.

14
00:01:35,666 --> 00:01:39,000
After that happened,
we haven't had any requests.

15
00:01:58,300 --> 00:01:59,886
Here's the schedule for this week.

16
00:01:59,966 --> 00:02:01,433
Ah, thank you.

17
00:02:03,533 --> 00:02:05,186
Um… Mr. Yeon?

18
00:02:05,266 --> 00:02:06,420
- Hmmm?
- Maybe it's time to

19
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:09,566
reconcile with Mr. Kwon.

20
00:02:09,866 --> 00:02:12,120
- What?
- Well, he's accepted it already,

21
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:13,686
so he can't go back on it now.

22
00:02:13,766 --> 00:02:16,253
And with no one to
turn to for support,

23
00:02:16,333 --> 00:02:17,453
just imagine how hard it must be

24
00:02:17,533 --> 00:02:19,400
if you're going to
keep up that attitude.

25
00:02:20,133 --> 00:02:21,500
What, you don't think
I'm having a hard time?

26
00:02:22,766 --> 00:02:26,053
How do you think I feel,
having to watch this and that?

27
00:02:26,133 --> 00:02:29,453
God, I should've known better
about his stubborn nature.

28
00:02:29,533 --> 00:02:31,200
Even back then, five years ago…

29
00:02:32,233 --> 00:02:33,266
Actually, no.

30
00:02:33,733 --> 00:02:35,120
Anyway, it's him who's done wrong,

31
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:38,353
so he should make the first move,
not me.

32
00:02:38,433 --> 00:02:40,300
Why should I give him
the special treatment?

33
00:02:40,833 --> 00:02:41,833
Go back to your work.

34
00:03:03,766 --> 00:03:04,920
(Is This the Park Su-myung Case,
Or the Lim Yun-hee Case?)

35
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,066
(Even the Judges Are Confused)

36
00:03:14,933 --> 00:03:16,320
What is it?

37
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:18,066
I had something to say.

38
00:03:23,766 --> 00:03:25,786
But your actions seemed to suggest
you'll never talk to me again.

39
00:03:25,866 --> 00:03:28,033
So, what is it that
you have to tell me?

40
00:03:34,333 --> 00:03:35,720
What is this?

41
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:36,933
A letter of apology?

42
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:39,866
It's a letter of resignation.

43
00:03:42,166 --> 00:03:43,586
What did you just say, Kwon?

44
00:03:43,666 --> 00:03:44,766
Resignation letter?

45
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:48,400
After accepting the
Park Su-myung case,

46
00:03:49,433 --> 00:03:51,700
I seem to have become
a great burden to the firm.

47
00:03:53,766 --> 00:03:56,653
My resignation would minimize
damages to the…

48
00:03:56,733 --> 00:03:59,420
Oh, so you'll quit?

49
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:02,700
After you create this mess,
you'll just run, and the end?

50
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:05,020
Is that what you are
really thinking, Kwon?

51
00:04:05,100 --> 00:04:08,233
Do you think resigning is
the best option?

52
00:04:09,233 --> 00:04:12,353
I will finish up on all my
current cases before I leave.

53
00:04:12,433 --> 00:04:13,466
Hey!

54
00:04:15,833 --> 00:04:17,633
You can't do this to me.

55
00:04:18,766 --> 00:04:20,566
You really can't do this to me,
you know that.

56
00:04:21,266 --> 00:04:23,153
I…

57
00:04:23,233 --> 00:04:26,853
I never considered you
as just an employee.

58
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:29,420
You are a friend I treasure and
a colleague whom I trust.

59
00:04:29,500 --> 00:04:32,120
You are more than family to me!

60
00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:35,020
Yet, first you accept a case under
your arbitrary decision,

61
00:04:35,100 --> 00:04:36,800
and next, you hand in
your resignation letter?

62
00:04:39,333 --> 00:04:42,020
But because of me, law firm
has come under fire and

63
00:04:42,100 --> 00:04:43,753
all those phone calls have been
holding everyone up in their work.

64
00:04:43,833 --> 00:04:45,486
Not only that, we've had
no new clients, have we?

65
00:04:45,566 --> 00:04:47,986
But despite all this…
I had to accept this case.

66
00:04:48,066 --> 00:04:50,420
I may have ruined someone's life,

67
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:52,233
so it's right I must
set things right again.

68
00:04:57,733 --> 00:05:00,420
That's why I had no other option.

69
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:01,553
Fine, do what you want.

70
00:05:01,633 --> 00:05:02,686
Do what you want!

71
00:05:02,766 --> 00:05:04,120
Because I also don't need
someone who is

72
00:05:04,200 --> 00:05:05,620
as irresponsible as you are.

73
00:05:05,700 --> 00:05:06,620
So do what you want!

74
00:05:06,700 --> 00:05:07,620
If you want to defend, defend!

75
00:05:07,700 --> 00:05:09,733
And if you want to resign,
all up to you.

76
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:23,220
Our defendant is an entrepreneur
and a self-made millionaire,

77
00:05:23,300 --> 00:05:26,353
with a total of $5 million in assets.

78
00:05:26,433 --> 00:05:28,953
However, he is refusing
a divorce on paper,

79
00:05:29,033 --> 00:05:33,233
because he does not wish to
pay his wife alimony…

80
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:38,266
…alimony, and…

81
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:42,833
…and so is refusing divorce…

82
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:56,886
My wish is to
never see you waiver.

83
00:05:56,966 --> 00:06:01,966
And just like you always have,
I'm sure you'll pull through this.

84
00:06:17,966 --> 00:06:19,053
Ah, Mr. Park.

85
00:06:19,133 --> 00:06:21,353
I see you're calling back
after I asked for your

86
00:06:21,433 --> 00:06:22,220
recommendations for lawyers.

87
00:06:22,300 --> 00:06:24,600
So, how did it go?

88
00:06:25,066 --> 00:06:28,220
No, I'm not fussed about winrates.

89
00:06:28,300 --> 00:06:29,820
As long as she or he has
a sense of responsibility,

90
00:06:29,900 --> 00:06:31,386
and doesn't stab you in the back
by producing

91
00:06:31,466 --> 00:06:33,300
a resignation letter out of blue.

92
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,066
Alright.

93
00:06:40,733 --> 00:06:42,353
Mr. Yeon.

94
00:06:42,433 --> 00:06:44,186
That's my phone…

95
00:06:44,266 --> 00:06:46,266
Yes, yes. I know!

96
00:06:52,366 --> 00:06:54,700
What to do about this atmosphere?

97
00:07:04,433 --> 00:07:05,620
(D-2 Until Park Su-myung's Appeal)

98
00:07:05,700 --> 00:07:07,333
(Does His Lawyer Have a Plan?)

99
00:07:23,533 --> 00:07:25,666
I wonder if he's alright.

100
00:07:28,733 --> 00:07:30,966
But I've no one to ask…

101
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:44,066
Wait, I'm sure I got
his number last time.

102
00:07:44,433 --> 00:07:46,400
(Prosecutor Kim Se-won)

103
00:08:00,966 --> 00:08:02,366
(Kim Se-won)

104
00:08:04,300 --> 00:08:05,353
Hello?

105
00:08:05,433 --> 00:08:06,353
Hey, where are you?

106
00:08:06,433 --> 00:08:07,566
Join me for a drink.

107
00:08:08,766 --> 00:08:10,253
No thanks, I'm beat.

108
00:08:10,333 --> 00:08:12,553
To tell you the truth…
Someone wants to see you.

109
00:08:12,633 --> 00:08:14,733
And this person says
they can't let you go like this.

110
00:08:18,066 --> 00:08:19,200
Just what…

111
00:08:29,466 --> 00:08:30,466
Hey, over here.

112
00:08:35,766 --> 00:08:37,233
Come on, don't just stand there.

113
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:47,366
Just sit already.

114
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:57,353
I was wondering what was up
when Jun-gyu called me.

115
00:08:57,433 --> 00:08:58,420
You're not in
middle school anymore.

116
00:08:58,500 --> 00:09:00,486
Grown-up adults don't fight!

117
00:09:00,566 --> 00:09:01,786
Oh, and Jung-rok.

118
00:09:01,866 --> 00:09:03,533
I heard you even turned in
your resignation letter.

119
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:08,053
Fine, I understand that
you decided to leave

120
00:09:08,133 --> 00:09:10,553
because you didn't want to be
a burden to the firm.

121
00:09:10,633 --> 00:09:13,853
Still, you should've talked it out
with Jun-gyu first.

122
00:09:13,933 --> 00:09:16,186
How could you just shove that
letter of resignation at his face?

123
00:09:16,266 --> 00:09:17,753
And from what he told me,

124
00:09:17,833 --> 00:09:20,453
he hasn't said anything wrong!

125
00:09:20,533 --> 00:09:21,420
What's so wrong with
his advice of,

126
00:09:21,500 --> 00:09:23,386
"Don't take a chance on
things you're unsure of?"

127
00:09:23,466 --> 00:09:25,186
What, can't he say that,
as your boss?

128
00:09:25,266 --> 00:09:27,653
Tsk, you narrow-minded bastard.

129
00:09:27,733 --> 00:09:30,620
But then again,
I did say something harsh.

130
00:09:30,700 --> 00:09:34,686
That he'll be branded a lawyer
who takes the Court for a show.

131
00:09:34,766 --> 00:09:37,986
Show? That was going too far.

132
00:09:38,066 --> 00:09:39,700
You're really brutal, aren't you?

133
00:09:41,033 --> 00:09:43,486
Just stop. It's my fault
anyway in the first place,

134
00:09:43,566 --> 00:09:45,420
for accepting the case
without asking for his permission.

135
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:46,853
What, you'd accepted the case

136
00:09:46,933 --> 00:09:48,533
without even
seeking his permission?

137
00:09:50,233 --> 00:09:52,686
You've no respect for
your boss, do you?

138
00:09:52,766 --> 00:09:54,653
Well, I must admit
I was being stubborn.

139
00:09:54,733 --> 00:09:57,386
It's not like Kwon has no manners…
It's alright.

140
00:09:57,466 --> 00:10:00,020
What, you knew that about him
and yet you were so stubborn?

141
00:10:00,100 --> 00:10:03,000
Jeez, you're really
uptight, aren't you?

142
00:10:05,100 --> 00:10:06,386
Are you here to help us
patch things up,

143
00:10:06,466 --> 00:10:07,420
or to fuel our anger?

144
00:10:07,500 --> 00:10:09,753
Make your stance clear.

145
00:10:09,833 --> 00:10:11,086
Did I…

146
00:10:11,166 --> 00:10:12,400
Did I confuse you?

147
00:10:15,100 --> 00:10:16,053
Anyway, from what I hear,

148
00:10:16,133 --> 00:10:18,786
both of you are equally at fault.

149
00:10:18,866 --> 00:10:22,486
That's what you call even, right?

150
00:10:22,566 --> 00:10:23,633
So drink. Here.

151
00:10:24,766 --> 00:10:26,533
Even?

152
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:28,466
So, anyway…

153
00:10:29,733 --> 00:10:32,053
Just make up already.

154
00:10:32,133 --> 00:10:33,166
Go on.

155
00:10:33,566 --> 00:10:34,900
Tsk, please…

156
00:10:36,466 --> 00:10:37,466
Oh what?

157
00:10:38,033 --> 00:10:39,620
Actually, this won't do.

158
00:10:39,700 --> 00:10:41,886
I'll go ahead first so you two
can talk things out.

159
00:10:41,966 --> 00:10:43,986
Hey, come on!
This isn't a blind date.

160
00:10:44,066 --> 00:10:45,453
Right, so stay a little longer.

161
00:10:45,533 --> 00:10:46,753
Hey, let go of me.

162
00:10:46,833 --> 00:10:47,886
I don't care how this
turns out anymore,

163
00:10:47,966 --> 00:10:50,086
you two talk and sort it out.

164
00:10:50,166 --> 00:10:51,266
Anyway, I'm off.

165
00:10:52,300 --> 00:10:53,420
Stay a little longer.

166
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:54,653
Hey, I said
stay just a little longer!

167
00:10:54,733 --> 00:10:57,566
- Oops.
- And he called me out here.

168
00:11:02,633 --> 00:11:04,433
I don't know
what's up with that guy.

169
00:11:06,233 --> 00:11:07,600
Ugh, please.

170
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:18,586
Prosecutor Kim,

171
00:11:18,666 --> 00:11:22,486
thank you for taking care of
the rest from last time.

172
00:11:22,566 --> 00:11:26,020
I remembered I was
yet to thank you for that.

173
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:31,366
Anyway, is Mr. Kwon doing okay?

174
00:11:38,333 --> 00:11:39,420
No.

175
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:40,953
This is too obvious.

176
00:11:41,033 --> 00:11:42,186
Anyone can see that

177
00:11:42,266 --> 00:11:45,333
I'm desperate to know
how Mr. Kwon is doing.

178
00:11:52,566 --> 00:11:54,020
But I can't ask the people
at the law firm anymore,

179
00:11:54,100 --> 00:11:56,433
because I used that card
too much already…

180
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,233
Kwon.

181
00:12:16,300 --> 00:12:17,433
I mean, Jung-rok.

182
00:12:19,666 --> 00:12:21,133
Don't you know me already?

183
00:12:23,933 --> 00:12:27,786
Did you really think
I would turn against you

184
00:12:27,866 --> 00:12:30,286
and kick you out of the firm?

185
00:12:30,366 --> 00:12:32,786
Did all that time
we spent together

186
00:12:32,866 --> 00:12:35,833
mean nothing to you?

187
00:12:40,166 --> 00:12:42,220
I'm sorry.

188
00:12:42,300 --> 00:12:44,586
But it's as you said.

189
00:12:44,666 --> 00:12:49,433
You asked me, if I never
considered Always as family.

190
00:12:51,800 --> 00:12:54,320
And you were right in
pointing that out.

191
00:12:54,400 --> 00:12:56,220
Because I…

192
00:12:56,300 --> 00:12:59,600
I've been selfish and tyrannical
from the start to the end.

193
00:13:02,766 --> 00:13:05,286
I started this

194
00:13:05,366 --> 00:13:08,133
in order to feel better and
be proud of myself,

195
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:14,000
so I thought it was right that
I take on all the criticisms alone.

196
00:13:14,900 --> 00:13:18,500
Therefore, the best option
I had before me,

197
00:13:19,700 --> 00:13:21,966
in order not to put any more
burden on you or Always,

198
00:13:23,800 --> 00:13:25,366
was to resign.

199
00:13:25,900 --> 00:13:26,966
I know.

200
00:13:28,566 --> 00:13:29,566
I know very well.

201
00:13:32,166 --> 00:13:34,966
I know how you felt
when you made that decision.

202
00:13:36,366 --> 00:13:38,386
But you know,

203
00:13:38,466 --> 00:13:41,320
I can't see you get hurt anymore.

204
00:13:41,400 --> 00:13:46,286
It's obvious you'll end up hurt
just like five years ago,

205
00:13:46,366 --> 00:13:48,386
and yet you want me to
just stand there,

206
00:13:48,466 --> 00:13:50,833
watching you walk that path?

207
00:13:53,633 --> 00:13:54,733
Jung-rok.

208
00:13:58,500 --> 00:14:01,633
Do you know what the
biggest regret I have in my life is?

209
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:13,400
It looks like we'll have to
stand on the side of the victims.

210
00:14:13,766 --> 00:14:14,830
(Five Years Ago)

211
00:14:14,833 --> 00:14:16,886
All of their claims
turned out to be true.

212
00:14:16,966 --> 00:14:20,686
That disinfectant does
clearly have toxicity.

213
00:14:20,766 --> 00:14:22,786
The research reports that claim
they're not toxic

214
00:14:22,866 --> 00:14:27,220
had reached that conclusion
after manipulating the

215
00:14:27,300 --> 00:14:29,520
testing conditions
in favor of Sejong Chemicals.

216
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:30,666
But what…

217
00:14:31,966 --> 00:14:35,586
Still, your client is
Sejong Chemicals.

218
00:14:35,666 --> 00:14:38,133
Is your boss even aware of this?

219
00:14:40,266 --> 00:14:42,520
I think

220
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:44,853
he may also be involved
in the manipulation.

221
00:14:44,933 --> 00:14:46,000
Hey.

222
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:50,133
Don't tell me…

223
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:52,266
You're not thinking of
disclosing this, are you?

224
00:14:53,800 --> 00:14:55,266
No way. There's just no way.

225
00:14:56,466 --> 00:14:58,720
The number of victims
amount to 250.

226
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:01,620
Even if I am representing
a corporate this time,

227
00:15:01,700 --> 00:15:04,986
am I not allowed the
tiniest bit of conscience?

228
00:15:05,066 --> 00:15:07,420
Hey, Jung-rok. Are you crazy?

229
00:15:07,500 --> 00:15:09,286
Don't even think of
doing the unthinkable.

230
00:15:09,366 --> 00:15:11,786
You know better than anyone else
about what Daehan Law is like.

231
00:15:11,866 --> 00:15:13,120
You…

232
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:14,866
You want to disclose this?

233
00:15:16,033 --> 00:15:19,233
If you do that,
you're finished as a lawyer.

234
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:23,466
I'm scared, too.

235
00:15:25,433 --> 00:15:26,986
But…

236
00:15:27,066 --> 00:15:29,553
But if I continue to
pretend I didn't see it,

237
00:15:29,633 --> 00:15:33,386
or hear it… Once, then twice…

238
00:15:33,466 --> 00:15:34,820
I'm afraid that I'll become

239
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:37,733
a desensitized monster that
they've become.

240
00:15:40,900 --> 00:15:42,300
And that's what scares me more.

241
00:15:48,833 --> 00:15:51,953
I'm thinking of bringing this up at
the Korean Bar Association to

242
00:15:52,033 --> 00:15:53,120
have your license revoked.

243
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:54,920
"Breaching of
confidentiality obligation."

244
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:56,786
I think that's enough
reason right there.

245
00:15:56,866 --> 00:16:00,586
Article 2-3 of the
Lawyer Code of Ethics states that

246
00:16:00,666 --> 00:16:03,286
a lawyer must not engage in
activities that

247
00:16:03,366 --> 00:16:04,386
undermine their dignity or
harm the public good,

248
00:16:04,466 --> 00:16:07,020
both during and outside his duties.

249
00:16:07,100 --> 00:16:08,986
As a lawyer,

250
00:16:09,066 --> 00:16:11,700
I'd like to hold onto
my conscience.

251
00:16:16,100 --> 00:16:19,686
Tsk, that Kwon Jung-rok…

252
00:16:19,766 --> 00:16:21,620
God, that…

253
00:16:21,700 --> 00:16:23,433
That crazy bastard!

254
00:16:31,800 --> 00:16:34,066
(Law Firm Yeram)

255
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:35,920
Good morning, sir.

256
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:38,833
I'm Yeon Jun-gyu, from the
32nd batch of graduates.

257
00:16:40,766 --> 00:16:43,720
