victimized by Daehan…

259
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:49,986
Since it's coming from you,
of course I should help.

260
00:16:50,066 --> 00:16:51,133
Thank you.

261
00:16:53,100 --> 00:16:55,886
I won't ever forget
what you did for me, sir.

262
00:16:55,966 --> 00:16:57,033
Thank you so much.

263
00:16:59,366 --> 00:17:01,853
The biggest regret
I hold in my life is

264
00:17:01,933 --> 00:17:05,266
not stopping you, five years ago.

265
00:17:07,600 --> 00:17:09,886
Because I saw with
my own two eyes,

266
00:17:09,966 --> 00:17:12,366
how you crumbled.

267
00:17:15,566 --> 00:17:17,286
Then…

268
00:17:17,366 --> 00:17:19,566
What do you think is the
best thing I did in my life is?

269
00:17:20,733 --> 00:17:24,100
Saving you, five years ago.

270
00:17:29,233 --> 00:17:31,520
Because that's how you came to
join me at my law firm,

271
00:17:31,600 --> 00:17:33,953
and from then on, we tackled
a lot of difficulties together.

272
00:17:34,033 --> 00:17:36,020
And while not much was
said between us,

273
00:17:36,100 --> 00:17:39,000
we came to rely each other a lot.

274
00:17:40,133 --> 00:17:41,900
That's who you are to me,

275
00:17:43,766 --> 00:17:45,733
so if you resign and leave,

276
00:17:50,866 --> 00:17:52,500
what will I have left in my life?

277
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:58,400
So let's walk down
this path together.

278
00:18:00,233 --> 00:18:01,233
I…

279
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:05,320
I can't see you break down
like this.

280
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:09,353
So even if it gets tough, let's…

281
00:18:09,433 --> 00:18:13,633
Let's brave it together. Alright?

282
00:19:09,766 --> 00:19:10,766
I…

283
00:19:13,000 --> 00:19:14,833
I won't be waivered, anymore.

284
00:19:26,733 --> 00:19:29,586
Do you think things will be
scary once again in the office?

285
00:19:29,666 --> 00:19:31,966
I know right.
It's been so scary lately.

286
00:19:33,400 --> 00:19:34,500
Good morning!

287
00:19:35,266 --> 00:19:37,220
- Ah, you're here.
- Ah, Dan. Mr. Lee.

288
00:19:37,300 --> 00:19:39,553
We'll have an urgent meeting
in 5 min, so get ready.

289
00:19:39,633 --> 00:19:41,853
- Oh, Pil-ki, go tell Choi.
- Yes, sir.

290
00:19:41,933 --> 00:19:44,153
So… Why this urgent meeting?

291
00:19:44,233 --> 00:19:45,986
Well, it's to save a life.

292
00:19:46,066 --> 00:19:47,986
Save a life? Whose?

293
00:19:48,066 --> 00:19:51,286
Who else? Kwon's, who's become
the nation's most hated lawyer.

294
00:19:51,366 --> 00:19:52,353
Nation's most hated lawyer?

295
00:19:52,433 --> 00:19:53,653
But it's true, isn't it?

296
00:19:53,733 --> 00:19:55,653
With all the complaint calls
and malicious comments,

297
00:19:55,733 --> 00:19:57,420
you are the nation's most hated.

298
00:19:57,500 --> 00:19:58,686
Get ready, then.

299
00:19:58,766 --> 00:19:59,920
Sure.

300
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,166
Then please.

301
00:20:04,200 --> 00:20:05,620
Oh what?

302
00:20:05,700 --> 00:20:06,820
Only just yesterday, it was as if

303
00:20:06,900 --> 00:20:08,253
they never wanted to
see each other again.

304
00:20:08,333 --> 00:20:09,853
Right?

305
00:20:09,933 --> 00:20:11,653
What do you think happened that

306
00:20:11,733 --> 00:20:14,386
their frozen hearts
melted once again?

307
00:20:14,466 --> 00:20:16,186
They probably had a drink
and talked it out.

308
00:20:16,266 --> 00:20:17,853
Let's get ready, then.

309
00:20:17,933 --> 00:20:19,033
Cut!

310
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,820
Cut! Alright!

311
00:20:25,900 --> 00:20:27,286
- Thanks everyone.
- Thank you everyone.

312
00:20:27,366 --> 00:20:28,286
Thank you, everyone.

313
00:20:28,366 --> 00:20:29,466
Thank you, everyone.

314
00:20:30,033 --> 00:20:31,966
- Thank you everyone.
- Good job, Yoon-seo.

315
00:20:32,633 --> 00:20:34,153
Thank you, everyone.

316
00:20:34,233 --> 00:20:35,266
Let's go.

317
00:20:35,900 --> 00:20:37,100
Thank you, everyone.

318
00:20:52,133 --> 00:20:53,300
Well done.

319
00:20:58,233 --> 00:21:00,766
Well done, Ms. Oh Jin-sim.

320
00:21:05,066 --> 00:21:06,720
What is it, Yoon-seo?

321
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:07,833
Just…

322
00:21:08,833 --> 00:21:10,566
I was just thinking about
Mr. Kwon.

323
00:21:11,566 --> 00:21:14,633
This is where we went on
a walk together.

324
00:21:26,100 --> 00:21:27,100
Huh?

325
00:21:28,333 --> 00:21:29,533
Wait here, Hyuk-jun.

326
00:21:31,800 --> 00:21:34,233
Um, excuse me! Prosecutor Kim!

327
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:37,266
Yoon-seo.

328
00:21:37,800 --> 00:21:39,586
What brings you here?

329
00:21:39,666 --> 00:21:41,686
We're shooting here today.

330
00:21:41,766 --> 00:21:44,000
Who knew I would
bump into you here like this?

331
00:21:45,066 --> 00:21:48,920
Because I've been wanting to
contact you.

332
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:50,286
Me?

333
00:21:50,366 --> 00:21:51,486
About what?

334
00:21:51,566 --> 00:21:52,933
Well, uh…

335
00:21:53,866 --> 00:21:55,653
Last time, uh…

336
00:21:55,733 --> 00:21:57,853
You dealt with that
stalking incident for me,

337
00:21:57,933 --> 00:21:59,953
and I wanted to say thank you.

338
00:22:00,033 --> 00:22:02,366
Oh, that!

339
00:22:02,700 --> 00:22:03,966
And, uh…

340
00:22:05,233 --> 00:22:07,520
Just be honest.

341
00:22:07,600 --> 00:22:10,020
You want to ask about
Jung-rok, don't you?

342
00:22:10,100 --> 00:22:12,266
You're as sharp as always.

343
00:22:16,100 --> 00:22:21,120
So… How is Mr. Kwon doing?

344
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:23,820
The media didn't seem to
be on his side.

345
00:22:23,900 --> 00:22:25,286
Is he alright?

346
00:22:25,366 --> 00:22:26,600
Of course not.

347
00:22:27,933 --> 00:22:31,320
Jung-rok hasn't been eating well
ever since he accepted the case,

348
00:22:31,400 --> 00:22:33,800
and I'm worried he may
collapse at this rate.

349
00:22:36,366 --> 00:22:38,600
Yoon-seo, we should get going.

350
00:22:40,133 --> 00:22:42,300
Otherwise you'll be late for
your next schedule.

351
00:22:45,633 --> 00:22:47,486
Um… I should get going.

352
00:22:47,566 --> 00:22:48,633
Sure.

353
00:22:49,400 --> 00:22:52,486
Please take good care of…

354
00:22:52,566 --> 00:22:54,133
…Mr. Kwon.

355
00:23:03,600 --> 00:23:05,753
Maybe I shouldn't have said it.

356
00:23:05,833 --> 00:23:07,666
It seems to have
bothered her greatly.

357
00:23:10,133 --> 00:23:12,033
But then again, that was
exactly the reason why I said it.

358
00:23:13,100 --> 00:23:14,920
This is Ms. Lim Yun-hee,

359
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:17,320
who was charged for
murdering her husband

360
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:18,786
on January 21, 2019,

361
00:23:18,866 --> 00:23:21,700
by stabbing him twice with a knife
when he started to beat her.

362
00:23:24,166 --> 00:23:27,953
The Prosecution found it
suspicious that

363
00:23:28,033 --> 00:23:30,220
Ms. Lim's father was
missing long-term,

364
00:23:30,300 --> 00:23:32,033
and that her ex-husband had
also perished in fire.

365
00:23:32,333 --> 00:23:34,753
Because straight after
their death was legally recognized,

366
00:23:34,833 --> 00:23:36,320
Ms. Lim received
a huge life insurance payout

367
00:23:36,400 --> 00:23:38,966
under their names.

368
00:23:40,266 --> 00:23:44,053
The Court ruled 20 years of
imprisonment for Mr. Park,

369
00:23:44,133 --> 00:23:46,353
and released Ms. Lim on bail.

370
00:23:46,433 --> 00:23:47,686
And as of current, Ms. Lim's
whereabouts are unknown

371
00:23:47,766 --> 00:23:51,920
after claiming only a portion of
the $4.93 million payout,

372
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:53,453
or $2.73 million, to be exact.

373
00:23:53,533 --> 00:23:55,086
Her whereabouts are unknown?

374
00:23:55,166 --> 00:23:57,686
Was she in a hurry? Why not wait
for the rest to come in?

375
00:23:57,766 --> 00:23:59,586
Something is fishy, yes.

376
00:23:59,666 --> 00:24:00,986
And right at this timing,
Park Su-myung has

377
00:24:01,066 --> 00:24:02,386
made a new claim.

378
00:24:02,466 --> 00:24:04,153
That he'd only stabbed him once.

379
00:24:04,233 --> 00:24:07,653
If what he said were true
and he had only stabbed him once,

380
00:24:07,733 --> 00:24:09,453
then that means the
true murderer may be out there,

381
00:24:09,533 --> 00:24:10,953
or he had an accomplice.

382
00:24:11,033 --> 00:24:12,933
Do you have any evidence to
support that?

383
00:24:13,966 --> 00:24:15,920
While tracking Ms. Lim,

384
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:18,053
we secured evidence that
she had been unaccompanied by

385
00:24:18,133 --> 00:24:21,033
an unidentified man to
receive the insurance payout.

386
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:24,020
But her records show that
she has no other family.

387
00:24:24,100 --> 00:24:25,533
What, already?

388
00:24:27,066 --> 00:24:29,853
But it hasn't been that long
since her husband died.

389
00:24:29,933 --> 00:24:31,453
Or…!

390
00:24:31,533 --> 00:24:34,286
Their relationship could have
started long before the murder.

391
00:24:34,366 --> 00:24:37,286
Because as you all know,
I'm quite an expert when

392
00:24:37,366 --> 00:24:40,186
it comes down to ugly love affairs
and divorce cases.

393
00:24:40,266 --> 00:24:41,953
And my instincts are telling me,

394
00:24:42,033 --> 00:24:43,120
it's her lover.

395
00:24:43,200 --> 00:24:44,300
Hold on.

396
00:24:45,100 --> 00:24:48,686
You said Lim's ex-husband also
perished in fire 5 years ago.

397
00:24:48,766 --> 00:24:51,620
Then we have reason to suspect
that this too, was the work of

398
00:24:51,700 --> 00:24:55,786
Lim and her lover.

399
00:24:55,866 --> 00:24:57,953
They're still suspicions.

400
00:24:58,033 --> 00:25:00,653
I think the first thing
on our list is to

401
00:25:00,733 --> 00:25:01,653
identify the man in that
security camera footage.

402
00:25:01,733 --> 00:25:03,853
Alright. Then Mr. Lee,

403
00:25:03,933 --> 00:25:06,553
please track down where Lim
headed after she was released.

404
00:25:06,633 --> 00:25:10,753
Please also search all the security
cameras in the vicinity,

405
00:25:10,833 --> 00:25:14,620
because there has to be a footage
of them, together somewhere.

406
00:25:14,700 --> 00:25:15,886
Yes, sir.

407
00:25:15,966 --> 00:25:17,886
By the way, Mr. Yeon.

408
00:25:17,966 --> 00:25:20,866
I haven't seen this charismatic
side of yours for a long time!

409
00:25:21,466 --> 00:25:22,586
I must agree.

410
00:25:22,666 --> 00:25:24,220
I'd temporarily forgotten,

411
00:25:24,300 --> 00:25:26,553
that you're a lawyer, too.

412
00:25:26,633 --> 00:25:27,633
Lawyer Yeon.

413
00:25:29,400 --> 00:25:31,086
Cut it with that.

414
00:25:31,166 --> 00:25:32,253
Yeon…

415
00:25:32,333 --> 00:25:33,520
Hey.

416
00:25:33,600 --> 00:25:36,066
Do you know why I took out a loan
and started my own office?

417
00:25:36,600 --> 00:25:39,420
"Prosecutor Yeon,"
"Judge Yeon." Sounds so natural.

418
00:25:39,500 --> 00:25:41,686
But what happens when
that's replaced with, "lawyer?"

419
00:25:41,766 --> 00:25:42,953
Lawyer Yeon…

420
00:25:43,033 --> 00:25:44,286
What the hell?

421
00:25:44,366 --> 00:25:46,053
It sounds like a swear word,
and I hate vulgar words.

422
00:25:46,133 --> 00:25:49,633
That's why, I became the
Representing Lawyer instead.

423
00:25:50,600 --> 00:25:52,566
- Lawyer Yeon…
- Hey!

424
00:25:54,866 --> 00:25:56,653
Alright, if you happen to
think of something,

425
00:25:56,733 --> 00:25:58,520
let's have a meeting again
and talk about it.

426
00:25:58,600 --> 00:25:59,753
Sure.

427
00:25:59,833 --> 00:26:00,753
Good job, team.

428
00:26:00,833 --> 00:26:02,253
Um, Mr. Kwon?

429
00:26:02,333 --> 00:26:03,386
If there's anything I can
help you with,

430
00:26:03,466 --> 00:26:04,686
don't hesitate to tell me.

431
00:26:04,766 --> 00:26:06,600
Alright, thank you.

432
00:26:07,433 --> 00:26:09,553
At times like these, it would be
good for him to

433
00:26:09,633 --> 00:26:10,686
have his own personal assistant.

434
00:26:10,766 --> 00:26:12,320
Should I find
a secretary for him, then?

435
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:14,986
But Ms. Hwang will be back from
her maternity leave in 3 months,

436
00:26:15,066 --> 00:26:17,520
so the timing isn't so right.

437
00:26:17,600 --> 00:26:19,066
You're right. Then…

438
00:26:19,633 --> 00:26:22,420
Why don't we take
one of the interns, and…

439
00:26:22,500 --> 00:26:24,620
I… I am here! Pil-ki is here!

440
00:26:24,700 --> 00:26:26,486
I can do better than Jong-hwa.

441
00:26:26,566 --> 00:26:28,153
So please give me a chance!

442
00:26:28,233 --> 00:26:30,386
This is a golden chance that
won't come again,

443
00:26:30,466 --> 00:26:32,520
and I don't want to miss it.

444
00:26:32,600 --> 00:26:33,920
Sure, then you do it.

445
00:26:34,000 --> 00:26:36,486
That means we had one applicant
for that one vacancy,

446
00:26:36,566 --> 00:26:38,020
and you beat some
hard competition.

447
00:26:38,100 --> 00:26:39,153
Congratulations to you.

448
00:26:39,233 --> 00:26:40,453
Anyway, let's make
preparations, then.

449
00:26:40,533 --> 00:26:41,666
Yes, sir.

450
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:07,620
I was searching up some
relevant case examples.

451
00:27:07,700 --> 00:27:10,153
In case they might help.

452
00:27:10,233 --> 00:27:11,220
Who knows?

453
00:27:11,300 --> 00:27:14,666
I might catch something that
you may miss.

454
00:27:15,133 --> 00:27:18,400
Hmm… I'd like to help, somehow.

455
00:27:23,366 --> 00:27:24,433
Yes?

456
00:27:27,100 --> 00:27:28,953
From today onward,

457
00:27:29,033 --> 00:27:31,520
Pil-ki here will
support you in your work.

458
00:27:31,600 --> 00:27:32,720
He'll be your personal assistant.

459
00:27:32,800 --> 00:27:35,220
I, Kim Pil-ki,

460
00:27:35,300 --> 00:27:36,820
vow to become an ace intern

461
00:27:36,900 --> 00:27:38,786
so as not to shame you sir,
who is an ace attorney.

462
00:27:38,866 --> 00:27:40,433
I'll be in your care, then.

463
00:27:41,166 --> 00:27:43,520
I know he tends to overexaggerate,
but he's a diligent guy.

464
00:27:43,600 --> 00:27:45,220
- I'll leave you to it, then.
- Yes, sir.

465
00:27:45,300 --> 00:27:46,300
Sure.

466
00:27:46,966 --> 00:27:49,953
Mr. Kwon, what would you
like me to do from now on?

467
00:27:50,033 --> 00:27:51,286
If you want me to
research case examples,

468
00:27:51,366 --> 00:27:54,833
I will do so until
I pull a ligament.

469
00:28:00,166 --> 00:28:02,686
Oh, sure. Then please look up
some case examples for me.

470
00:28:02,766 --> 00:28:04,166
Yes, sir.

471
00:28:06,900 --> 00:28:08,753
Mr. Kwon, would you like help?

472
00:28:08,833 --> 00:28:10,186
No…

473
00:28:10,266 --> 00:28:11,566
Alright, then.

474
00:28:26,833 --> 00:28:29,220
Where are you off to, Mr. Kwon?

475
00:28:29,300 --> 00:28:30,986
I'm off to the Archives.

476
00:28:31,066 --> 00:28:32,353
There's a reference I need.

477
00:28:32,433 --> 00:28:34,320
Alright, then. Let me escort you.

478
00:28:34,400 --> 00:28:36,186
No, that's alright.

479
00:28:36,266 --> 00:28:39,253
Just take notes down
if there are any calls.

480
00:28:39,333 --> 00:28:41,720
And there should be a diary
inside that desk.

481
00:28:41,800 --> 00:28:43,420
You'll find your duties
listed in there.

482
00:28:43,500 --> 00:28:44,420
Yes, sir.

483
00:28:44,500 --> 00:28:46,186
Oh, and Mr. Kwon.

484
00:28:46,266 --> 00:28:48,886
It'll be lunch soon, so…

485
00:28:48,966 --> 00:28:50,720
Would you like me to
grab something for you?

486
00:28:50,800 --> 00:28:52,586
It's alright,
I'll take care of myself.

487
00:28:52,666 --> 00:28:54,220
- Then.
- Alright.

488
00:28:54,300 --> 00:28:55,366
Goodbye, sir.

489
00:29:03,966 --> 00:29:05,520
Even though he's been
driven to a corner,

490
00:29:05,600 --> 00:29:07,233
