00:30:28,466 --> 00:30:31,086
So I'm at your old desk right now,

516
00:30:31,166 --> 00:30:36,020
and happened to discover
the pen you left behind.

517
00:30:36,100 --> 00:30:38,720
Um, if it's alright with you,

518
00:30:38,800 --> 00:30:41,700
may I keep this pen as a keepsake?

519
00:30:42,700 --> 00:30:43,800
Sure, do that.

520
00:30:45,600 --> 00:30:48,500
Um, hold on.

521
00:30:57,366 --> 00:30:58,786
Yes, Mr. Lee.

522
00:30:58,866 --> 00:31:00,153
Um…

523
00:31:00,233 --> 00:31:03,120
We did some legwork using the
security camera footage,

524
00:31:03,200 --> 00:31:04,766
but to no avail.

525
00:31:06,500 --> 00:31:10,166
Alright, I see.

526
00:31:18,833 --> 00:31:20,353
Welcome back, Mr. Kwon.

527
00:31:20,433 --> 00:31:21,500
Yes, well…

528
00:31:23,000 --> 00:31:24,720
Any important calls
while I was out?

529
00:31:24,800 --> 00:31:26,553
No, no important calls.

530
00:31:26,633 --> 00:31:29,933
But you do have a VIP guest.

531
00:31:30,800 --> 00:31:32,386
Um…

532
00:31:32,466 --> 00:31:35,386
I found Ms. Oh's pen
in the drawers.

533
00:31:35,466 --> 00:31:37,720
So I contacted her,

534
00:31:37,800 --> 00:31:39,900
and she came to pick it up.

535
00:31:40,900 --> 00:31:44,853
I said I could send it
to her by post,

536
00:31:44,933 --> 00:31:47,453
but she said it was
really important to her,

537
00:31:47,533 --> 00:31:49,086
and that she'll have to
come in person to pick it up.

538
00:31:49,166 --> 00:31:52,333
And so here she is now.

539
00:31:55,000 --> 00:31:57,486
Well, Mr. Yeon called for me,

540
00:31:57,566 --> 00:31:59,966
so I better go and see him.

541
00:32:25,633 --> 00:32:27,420
Well, uh…

542
00:32:27,500 --> 00:32:29,866
I came to pick up my pen,

543
00:32:31,833 --> 00:32:33,666
but thought I should say hello
before I left.

544
00:32:43,133 --> 00:32:46,620
Those are the files
I left for you.

545
00:32:46,700 --> 00:32:47,986
Yes.

546
00:32:48,066 --> 00:32:49,286
I know.

547
00:32:49,366 --> 00:32:52,086
What, you knew,

548
00:32:52,166 --> 00:32:54,400
and you never called to
say thank you?

549
00:32:55,733 --> 00:32:58,933
You should've said thanks
if you've received it.

550
00:33:02,800 --> 00:33:04,886
I want my compensation.

551
00:33:04,966 --> 00:33:06,953
I gave you such useful data,

552
00:33:07,033 --> 00:33:09,920
so you should reciprocate
my efforts.

553
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:11,986
Article 734 of the
Civil Act states,

554
00:33:12,066 --> 00:33:15,553
"A person who manages affairs
on behalf of another without

555
00:33:15,633 --> 00:33:16,953
being bound to do so has
the right to seek compensation for

556
00:33:17,033 --> 00:33:18,266
the costs incurred."

557
00:33:20,733 --> 00:33:22,520
Don't tell me you don't know.

558
00:33:22,600 --> 00:33:24,353
So anyway,

559
00:33:24,433 --> 00:33:26,820
as my compensation…

560
00:33:26,900 --> 00:33:28,033
Treat me to lunch or dinner.

561
00:33:31,033 --> 00:33:32,133
Or…

562
00:33:34,200 --> 00:33:35,733
Should I treat you instead?

563
00:33:37,033 --> 00:33:39,486
But then again, that was
something you didn't really

564
00:33:39,566 --> 00:33:42,620
ask me to do, and
I guess it could be a burden.

565
00:33:42,700 --> 00:33:47,566
As my apology, let me treat you.

566
00:33:48,533 --> 00:33:50,020
What should we have, then?

567
00:33:50,100 --> 00:33:52,066
Pick something that's healthy.

568
00:33:53,266 --> 00:33:54,433
Ms. Oh Jin-sim.

569
00:33:56,666 --> 00:33:57,733
Have you forgotten that…

570
00:33:59,366 --> 00:34:01,500
…we broke up?

571
00:34:08,500 --> 00:34:10,533
How can I forget?

572
00:34:12,766 --> 00:34:15,766
Of course I know. But…

573
00:34:20,200 --> 00:34:23,520
But I'm worried about you.

574
00:34:23,600 --> 00:34:26,686
It's been so hard for you
these days, hasn't it?

575
00:34:26,766 --> 00:34:30,366
I saw the news, and
it really hurt my heart.

576
00:34:33,100 --> 00:34:37,900
You'd be there for me,
when I was having a hard time,

577
00:34:42,833 --> 00:34:45,000
but I can't, can I?

578
00:34:48,900 --> 00:34:51,133
Because we're not in that
kind of relationship anymore.

579
00:34:57,066 --> 00:34:58,853
Still, I came.

580
00:34:58,933 --> 00:35:01,120
'What if he hates it?'
'What if I end up troubling him?'

581
00:35:01,200 --> 00:35:05,886
I asked myself,
but still, I'm here.

582
00:35:05,966 --> 00:35:08,000
Because I wanted to
have lunch or dinner with you.

583
00:35:11,666 --> 00:35:15,653
Because I was worried
you'd collapse from overwork.

584
00:35:15,733 --> 00:35:19,033
You don't need to worry about
such a thing.

585
00:35:21,133 --> 00:35:24,453
- Pardon?
- Because as you said,

586
00:35:24,533 --> 00:35:26,833
we're not in that kind of
relationship anymore.

587
00:35:30,733 --> 00:35:34,953
- Mr. Kwon…
- So instead of worrying about me,

588
00:35:35,033 --> 00:35:38,400
I hope you'll put all your efforts
into your given duties.

589
00:35:40,200 --> 00:35:42,766
Try to forget about
all that happened here.

590
00:37:06,200 --> 00:37:09,420
Oh what? You were at home,
so why didn't you get the door?

591
00:37:09,500 --> 00:37:11,286
Yoon-seo, I bought some
health supplements that are

592
00:37:11,366 --> 00:37:12,886
supposed to be
good for your health,

593
00:37:12,966 --> 00:37:15,233
and also abalone porridge,
which are even better!

594
00:37:17,100 --> 00:37:18,453
What is it?

595
00:37:18,533 --> 00:37:19,966
Did something happen?

596
00:37:21,066 --> 00:37:23,720
All the notes were gone.

597
00:37:23,800 --> 00:37:26,053
- Huh?
- I was told that

598
00:37:26,133 --> 00:37:28,533
Mr. Kwon is having
a hard time these days.

599
00:37:30,800 --> 00:37:35,953
So I went to see him
because I was so worried,

600
00:37:36,033 --> 00:37:39,833
but he didn't look at me
with that warm gaze anymore.

601
00:37:41,400 --> 00:37:44,466
And all those notes that
we had exchanged…

602
00:37:46,533 --> 00:37:48,266
He'd taken them all off.

603
00:37:51,800 --> 00:37:54,853
I guess…

604
00:37:54,933 --> 00:37:57,400
…he's really over me now.

605
00:38:03,400 --> 00:38:05,533
But what about me?

606
00:38:17,433 --> 00:38:19,820
So… Why did Yoon-seo say
she came here?

607
00:38:19,900 --> 00:38:23,386
Oh, she left a pen behind
and came to pick it up.

608
00:38:23,466 --> 00:38:25,986
She's so busy, yet she came
all this way for a pen?

609
00:38:26,066 --> 00:38:28,733
I guess that pen must be
really important to her.

610
00:38:29,866 --> 00:38:31,966
I think I understand her.

611
00:38:33,733 --> 00:38:35,186
Everyone has things that are
special to them,

612
00:38:35,266 --> 00:38:37,486
even if they may be
worthless to other people.

613
00:38:37,566 --> 00:38:39,953
For example,

614
00:38:40,033 --> 00:38:43,633
I have this leaf bookmark

615
00:38:44,833 --> 00:38:46,366
which I picked up on my way to
my grandmother's house.

616
00:38:47,333 --> 00:38:49,020
If I were to lose it,

617
00:38:49,100 --> 00:38:52,133
I think I would be overcome by
extreme sadness.

618
00:39:22,700 --> 00:39:23,766
Mr. Kwon.

619
00:39:26,833 --> 00:39:29,653
We did manage to obtain
additional footage,

620
00:39:29,733 --> 00:39:31,286
but still, there was
nothing that's noteworthy.

621
00:39:31,366 --> 00:39:33,420
But I did ask some people that
I know from my days

622
00:39:33,500 --> 00:39:35,233
as a detective to
look into it a bit more.

623
00:39:38,966 --> 00:39:40,953
What is it?

624
00:39:41,033 --> 00:39:43,853
Something's not quite right
about these articles.

625
00:39:43,933 --> 00:39:45,000
What is it?

626
00:39:46,333 --> 00:39:47,886
The blood splattered everywhere,

627
00:39:47,966 --> 00:39:49,633
for the wall to be
stained like this,

628
00:39:51,366 --> 00:39:55,166
but why is Mr. Park's
jacket so clean?

629
00:40:00,600 --> 00:40:02,933
(Court)

630
00:40:03,266 --> 00:40:04,653
The jacket you see on the screen

631
00:40:04,733 --> 00:40:07,853
was the jacket worn by
my client during his crime.

632
00:40:07,933 --> 00:40:10,253
Forensic testing has found
traces of the victim's blood

633
00:40:10,333 --> 00:40:12,120
on the sleeve,

634
00:40:12,200 --> 00:40:14,586
and this may be evidence that

635
00:40:14,666 --> 00:40:17,366
my client stabbed Kim Hyung-tae,

636
00:40:18,800 --> 00:40:23,200
and at the same time,
only stabbed him just once.

637
00:40:27,233 --> 00:40:29,386
The wound that proved fatal is

638
00:40:29,466 --> 00:40:31,853
the second on the victim's chest.

639
00:40:31,933 --> 00:40:35,220
The second stab tore the
artery to the heart,

640
00:40:35,300 --> 00:40:37,800
and the victim died from
excessive hemorrhage.

641
00:40:39,700 --> 00:40:41,586
As you can see from the
photo of the crime scene,

642
00:40:41,666 --> 00:40:44,066
the walls and the floor are
covered with blood.

643
00:40:44,400 --> 00:40:46,720
This is because as soon as
the killer pulled out the knife,

644
00:40:46,800 --> 00:40:48,720
blood splattered everywhere,
like a leaking pipe.

645
00:40:48,800 --> 00:40:50,720
And it is hard to understand that
in such a situation,

646
00:40:50,800 --> 00:40:53,520
only a trace amount of blood
was detected on my client's

647
00:40:53,600 --> 00:40:55,433
jacket, when he is supposedly
responsible for the fatal stab.

648
00:40:57,633 --> 00:41:00,120
Moreover, Ms. Lim Yun-hee,
who was released on bail

649
00:41:00,200 --> 00:41:03,353
has recently gone dark
after collecting only $2.73 million

650
00:41:03,433 --> 00:41:06,966
of the $4.93 million that
she is entitled to.

651
00:41:08,100 --> 00:41:10,953
What could be the reason
she went into hiding,

652
00:41:11,033 --> 00:41:13,700
even giving up on
what amounts to over $2 million?

653
00:41:16,033 --> 00:41:18,020
Can we still argue that

654
00:41:18,100 --> 00:41:20,086
the Prosecution has
put forward enough evidence to

655
00:41:20,166 --> 00:41:21,853
support their claims that
they have no reason to

656
00:41:21,933 --> 00:41:23,766
doubt that Mr. Park Su-myung is
the true murderer?

657
00:41:25,766 --> 00:41:28,600
(Judge)

658
00:41:27,933 --> 00:41:30,100
Counsel, you may defend.

659
00:41:35,233 --> 00:41:37,900
Your Honor, I would like to
call a witness to the stand.

660
00:41:38,233 --> 00:41:40,233
She is the only witness of
the crime,

661
00:41:50,733 --> 00:41:52,900
- Ms. Lim Yun-hee.
- Yun-hee!

662
00:41:59,333 --> 00:42:00,366
Yun-hee!

663
00:42:05,966 --> 00:42:07,166
(Witness)

664
00:42:10,766 --> 00:42:11,800
Ms. Lim.

665
00:42:13,266 --> 00:42:16,466
May I ask why you had
cut off all contact all this time?

666
00:42:18,233 --> 00:42:21,653
After I was released on bail,

667
00:42:21,733 --> 00:42:23,766
I went on a trip to clear my head.

668
00:42:25,666 --> 00:42:27,286
I see.

669
00:42:27,366 --> 00:42:30,353
Then let me ask you, Ms. Lim,
who was once the suspect,

670
00:42:30,433 --> 00:42:33,553
and now the sole witness of
this murder case.

671
00:42:33,633 --> 00:42:35,153
Who is the culprit that
killed the victim,

672
00:42:35,233 --> 00:42:38,366
by stabbing him twice?

673
00:42:43,833 --> 00:42:45,766
Yun-hee! Yun-hee!

674
00:42:47,600 --> 00:42:48,700
Su-myung…

675
00:42:51,066 --> 00:42:52,733
I'm sorry, Su-myung.

676
00:42:53,966 --> 00:42:56,820
Yun-hee, don't cry. Don't cry!

677
00:42:56,900 --> 00:42:58,500
Yun-hee, don't cry.

678
00:43:00,733 --> 00:43:02,220
Ms. Lim.

679
00:43:02,300 --> 00:43:03,886
Let me ask you again.

680
00:43:03,966 --> 00:43:06,820
Was it Mr. Park Su-myung,
who is sitting over there,

681
00:43:06,900 --> 00:43:10,033
that murdered your husband by
stabbing him once

682
00:43:10,966 --> 00:43:14,566
in the abdomen, and
then in the chest?

683
00:43:17,633 --> 00:43:20,500
Yes, it was.

684
00:43:24,933 --> 00:43:26,100
I rest my case.

685
00:43:32,700 --> 00:43:34,733
Yun-hee.

686
00:43:51,933 --> 00:43:53,853
- Ms. Lim!
- Mr. Kwon.

687
00:43:53,933 --> 00:43:55,653
You claimed Ms. Lim Yun-hee
had gone into hiding.

688
00:43:55,733 --> 00:43:57,020
So what do you have to say
about how she was

689
00:43:57,100 --> 00:43:57,986
present in court today to
stand as witness?

690
00:43:58,066 --> 00:44:00,353
Do you truly believe the true
murderer is out there?

691
00:44:00,433 --> 00:44:03,533
Many have criticized you for
choosing to defend Mr. Park…

692
00:44:05,466 --> 00:44:06,633
How did it go?

693
00:44:08,100 --> 00:44:09,486
How do you think it went?

694
00:44:09,566 --> 00:44:11,233
I knocked him out.

695
00:44:12,900 --> 00:44:15,653
Thank God we got in touch with
Lim Yun-hee just before the trial.

696
00:44:15,733 --> 00:44:17,533
Otherwise it may have been
a close one.

697
00:44:18,266 --> 00:44:19,333
By the way,

698
00:44:21,066 --> 00:44:23,720
how were you suddenly able to
get in touch with her?

699
00:44:23,800 --> 00:44:26,153
Well… She called us first.

700
00:44:26,233 --> 00:44:27,766
Saying she wanted to
stand as witness.

701
00:44:32,666 --> 00:44:34,186
(Lim Yun-hee Stands As Witness
for the Park Murder Case)

702
00:44:33,633 --> 00:44:35,220
What happened here?

703
00:44:34,266 --> 00:44:35,566
(Amid Controversy)

704
00:44:35,300 --> 00:44:38,153
Kwon said he secured hard evidence
so this isn't what I expected.

705
00:44:38,233 --> 00:44:40,920
Right. I never expected
Lim Yun-hee to

706
00:44:41,000 --> 00:44:42,320
turn up at the trial.

707
00:44:42,400 --> 00:44:44,120
What do you think happened?

708
00:44:44,200 --> 00:44:46,186
Is Lim Yun-hee
innocent, after all?

709
00:44:46,266 --> 00:44:48,620
She probably appeared in Court
because she has nothing to hide.

710
00:44:48,700 --> 00:44:49,620
Oh, who knows.

711
00:44:49,700 --> 00:44:51,186
But the conclusion is,

712
00:44:51,266 --> 00:44:54,000
more people are criticizing
Mr. Kwon as a result.

713
00:45:05,233 --> 00:45:08,020
Gosh, Yoon-seo. Stop reading it.

714
00:45:08,100 --> 00:45:10,233
It'll only make you feel worse.

715
00:45:28,933 --> 00:45:31,553
You know, I can't do this anymore.

716
00:45:31,633 --> 00:45:33,586
Yoon-seo? Actually…

717
00:45:33,666 --> 00:45:37,420
Before that,
slap me hard right here.

718
00:45:37,500 --> 00:45:39,253
Oh what? What's this about?

719
00:45:39,333 --> 00:45:41,153
I mean it.
I deserve to be slapped.

720
00:45:41,233 --> 00:45:42,753
Because I…

721
00:45:42,833 --> 00:45:45,353
I did something that
you'll hate me for.

722
00:45:45,433 --> 00:45:47,133
To tell you the truth,
Mr. Kwon, he…

723
00:45:48,600 --> 00:45:50,666
He didn't break up with you
because he doesn't love you.

724
00:46:11,500 --> 00:46:12,653
Yes, Mr. Lee.

725
00:46:12,733 --> 00:46:14,533
I got hold of the security camera.

726
00:46:20,200 --> 00:46:22,153
It's near the bank where
she withdrew the money.

727
00:46:22,233 --> 00:46:25,420
February 27th, 3 p.m…
It's that day alright.

728
00:46:25,500 --> 00:46:28,153
This is the one with the
best resolution,

729
00:46:28,233 --> 00:46:31,500
but it'll still be difficult to
make out his face.

730
00:46:37,800 --> 00:46:38,933
What is it?

731
00:46:45,233 --> 00:46:47,153
We don't have anything with
a clear shot of his face.

732
00:46:47,233 --> 00:46:48,466
But take a look at this.

733
00:46:50,333 --> 00:46:52,520
Do you think we can obtain
fingerprint samples?

734
00:46:52,600 --> 00:46:55,120
From what I see here,
I think it might be possible.

735
00:46:55,200 --> 00:46:56,433
That should do.

736
00:47:02,833 --> 00:47:04,553
He…

737
00:47:04,633 --> 00:47:06,433
He didn't leave you
because he doesn’t love you,

738
00:47:07,833 --> 00:47:11,066
but because
he loves you too much.

739
00:47:14,233 --> 00:47:15,233
Let's…

740
00:47:19,600 --> 00:47:21,653
…break up.

741
00:47:21,733 --> 00:47:23,686
Did you feel betrayed,
now that you thought about it?

742
00:47:23,766 --> 00:47:29,120
Or you felt burdened by
all this unwanted attention?

743
00:47:29,200 --> 00:47:32,053
It's because of all the
reasons you mentioned,

744
00:47:32,133 --> 00:47:35,586
that I decided it was too much for
me to continue our relationship.

745
00:47:35,666 --> 00:47:40,666
So I think it's best that
we leave it here.

746
00:47:44,400 --> 00:47:46,133
Those weren't the reasons.

747
00:48:20,033 --> 00:48:21,986
On your way to work, Mr. Kwon?

748
00:48:22,066 --> 00:48:23,720
- Why are you…
- I, uh…

749
00:48:23,800 --> 00:48:25,820
…packed lunch for you.

750
00:48:25,900 --> 00:48:26,900
Here.

751
00:48:28,466 --> 00:48:29,766
Enjoy your lunch,

752
00:48:31,966 --> 00:48:33,633
and don't skip your meals.

753
00:48:36,466 --> 00:48:37,886
Ms. Oh Jin-sim…

754
00:48:37,966 --> 00:48:40,286
Oh, it's time for my shoot.
I should get going.

755
00:48:40,366 --> 00:48:43,933
Eat that, cheer up,
and strike back!

756
00:48:46,333 --> 00:48:48,033
You need to eat
everything, alright?

757
00:49:06,233 --> 00:49:09,253
Mr. Kwon, would you like to
have dinner with me?

758
00:49:09,333 --> 00:49:12,053
I looked up this restaurant
that's usually empty,

759
00:49:12,133 --> 00:49:13,166
so let's go.

760
00:49:21,533 --> 00:49:23,020
Why are you doing this?

761
00:49:23,100 --> 00:49:25,866
If you continue to pop up
everywhere like this,

762
00:49:27,166 --> 00:49:29,120
someone may get our photo and
it may result in another scandal.

763
00:49:29,200 --> 00:49:30,653
As I told you,

764
00:49:30,733 --> 00:49:31,986
forget about
all that happened, and…

765
00:49:32,066 --> 00:49:33,400
I don't want to.

766
00:49:36,333 --> 00:49:38,920
It's me who chooses
whether to forget or not.

767
00:49:39,000 --> 00:49:42,653
I'm going to do what I want
and not forget about you.

768
